        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 2:13PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 213 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Fountain, or 14 miles southeast of Colorado
Springs, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Colorado Springs, Fountain, Hanover, Schriever Space
Force Base, and Security-Widefield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
